        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 2 at 9:24AM CDT until April 2 at 10:00AM CDT by NWS St Louis MO</headline>
        <description>At 924 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Pleasant Hill,
or 10 miles south of Pittsfield, moving northeast at 70 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Pittsfield, White Hall, Roodhouse, Pleasant Hill, Atlas,
Independence, Bedford, Patterson, Montezuma, Martinsburg, Nebo,
Milton, Hillview, Pearl, Detroit, Florence, Time, Valley City,
Beecreek and New Hartford.

This includes Interstate 72 near exit 35.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds.

Tornadoes can develop quickly from severe thunderstorms. Seek
shelter immediately in an interior room on the lowest floor of a
well-built structure.

Report severe weather to your nearest law enforcement agency or the
National Weather Service office in St Louis MO.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 PM CDT Wednesday for
portions of southwest and west central Illinois.</instruction>
